If some putz shoots me a tell in GD or some such begging for a port, I'll explain to them the beauty of the book if they have PoP, and if they whine that they don't have it, &quot;hey look! a wizzie spire!&quot; and go about my merry business.  <br>
If it's CS or something and there are only 2 others in zone besides whoevers &quot;ooc&quot; for a port, I usually do another quad or two of otter hurting, ask 'em if they still need port, and off we go.  At 62 I really don't care one way or the other about donation, if they want to that's fine, if they don't I'm not gonna be hurting for the 15 to 30pp I didn't get.  <br>
What usually screws them is sending me tells directly.  Again, if zone is totally empty, 2 to 3 people max...  I can kinda understand a tell as opposed to shouting across a quiet room, what would be the point?  But if there are some 30 people in zone...  Try ooc before you pester someone more than likely much higher lvl than you.<br>
And as far as spoiled noobs?  I have to bite back the mean remarks every time I see some lvl 25 snivle for a rezz in HHK.  ONLY reason you really need a rezz there...  If you're bound on the other ****ing end of norrath (it is after all a long ass walk even from the misty book &amp; Kith terrifies most low to even mid lvl chars).  OR if you're lvl 50ish maiming nobles...  Then the xp loss does rather much bite.  But bound at the bank and crying for the two blues you lost????  OMFG go kill 3 gobbies!!!<br>
And no I'm not totally cold hearted...  I do occasionally go to some totally random noob zone and offer to PL and give gimp gear (if needed) to some random noob I've never met before.  Some days it's just ooc buffs at noob lift, some days one person gets druid lovin' for 3 or 4 hours...  Just depends on my mood.  Granted much of the 3 to 4 hour style druid loving comes after I sit in a completely empty crushbone for an hour waiting for some noob to zone in.  All she saw was a blur of fur and about 30 orcs including crush.  After I stopped laughing I sent her a tell, offered her gear and sweet buffs (before the min lvl nerf) for being such a good sport about the whole thing.<br>
<br>
